---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Geology — Rock-Solid High Scores"
  description="Geology terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUARTZ (24pts), SCHIST (11pts), BASALT (8pts), GNEISS (7pts). Earth science vocabulary for competitive play."
  keywords="scrabble geology words, quartz scrabble points, basalt scrabble, gneiss scrabble, schist scrabble, rock words scrabble, geology vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Geology — Rock-Solid High Scores","description":"Geology terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. QUARTZ (24pts), SCHIST (11pts), BASALT (8pts), GNEISS (7pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-geology"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is QUARTZ worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"QUARTZ scores 24 points (Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10). It's one of the highest-scoring 6-letter words in the game, using both Q and Z tiles together."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is GNEISS a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! GNEISS scores 7 points (G=2, N=1, E=1, I=1, S=1, S=1). It's a type of metamorphic rock. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What geology words score highest in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Top geology words include QUARTZ (24pts), SCHIST (11pts), BASALT (8pts), and GNEISS (7pts). QUARTZ dominates thanks to Q=10 and Z=10 in the same word."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Geology — Rock-Solid High Scores</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Geology gives Scrabble players access to some of the game's most powerful words. QUARTZ alone scores 24 points — using both the Q and Z tiles in a single devastating play. Earth science vocabulary is a goldmine for competitive players who know their rocks.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">24 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUARTZ</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SCHIST</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BASALT</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GNEISS</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The King of Geology Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">QUARTZ — 24 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10 · 6 letters</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A crystalline mineral found worldwide. QUARTZ is the holy grail — it uses BOTH the Q=10 and Z=10 tiles in one word, delivering 24 base points. On a triple-word square, that's 72 points from a single play.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">�ite SCHIST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · S=1, C=3, H=4, I=1, S=1, T=1 · Metamorphic rock</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">�ite BASALT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · B=3, A=1, S=1, A=1, L=1, T=1 · Volcanic rock</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪨 GNEISS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · G=2, N=1, E=1, I=1, S=1, S=1 · Banded rock</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💎 GEODE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · G=2, E=1, O=1, D=2, E=1 · Crystal cavity</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Geology Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SHALE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SLATE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MAGMA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FLINT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHALK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STRATA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUARTZ is the Q+Z dream:</span> If you hold both Q and Z, QUARTZ only needs U, A, R, T — all common tiles. This is the single best word for dumping both premium tiles at once.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SCHIST uses the CH combo:</span> C=3 and H=4 together give 7 points from two tiles. SCHIST also uses double S, helping clear duplicate tiles from your rack.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUARTZITE extends to 9 letters:</span> If the board allows it, QUARTZITE (Q=10, U=1, A=1, R=1, T=1, Z=10, I=1, T=1, E=1 = 27pts + 50 bingo bonus = 77pts) is a game-winning play.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Geology is the <span class="text-white font-medium">Q-tile's best friend</span>. QUARTZ, QUARTZITE, and QUARTZ-based plays give you the highest-scoring options for disposing of the Q tile with a U available. Memorise these rock words.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-dinosaurs/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Dinosaurs</span></a>
